Finance Minister Says South Africa's Budget Deficit `Extremely Manageable'

-- B y   G o r d o n   B e l l
-- 
2011-02-24T06:18:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/finance-minister-says-south-africa-s-budget-deficit-extremely-manageable-.html
  South Africa ’s budget deficit of 5.3
percent of gross domestic product is “extremely manageable,”
Finance Minister  Pravin Gordhan  said in an interview on SAFM
radio today.  The government won’t impose austerity measures on the
population to bring the deficit down faster, Gordhan said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
